This paper deals with interference coordination in heterogeneous networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization and resource allocation, which are topics related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also deals with system-level issues and coordination between different entities, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions resource block allocation and user association, which are topics related to multimedia and communication, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves distributed algorithms, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
